      • askForOptions

        void askForOptions(Options options,
                 java.util.Scanner scan)
        Prompts user for inputs to put into the Options Object and scans the input. If the input is incorrect, it will reprompt for input.
        Parameters:
        options - The option input from the Scanner.
        scan - The scanner for the option input.

      • check

        boolean check(java.lang.String input,
            Options options)
        Method that checks a string for line length, returning true if the string contains more characters than the number specified when constructing the LineWidth object and false if the line is too long.
        Parameters:
        input - The string the method is checking.
        options - The options object that has the information on the check.
        Returns:
        True if the string contains the correct length and false if not.

      • error

        java.lang.String error(int line)
        Method that simply returns the proper error message for a line containing improper length.
        Parameters:
        line - The line number that the error occured
        Returns:
        The error message.
